<p>I was using the Internet for several years before the Web came
along,
and I have been using the web since ancient times -- in the early
1990s.
I remember the excitement of the first browser and the first search
engine
- the web actually functioned for a couple of years without either one!
</p>
<p>Since then, I have used the Web in a variety of ways, and have spent
a lot of time thinking and reading about what the web is, how it can be
used, and what its limitations and dangers might be. This part of my
web
site is devoted to the Web itself. It is a collection of resources on
the
web about the web, from tools for the beginner to more advanced
readings
for experienced users and resources for professional educators
interested
in the pedagogical uses of the web.
</p>
<h3><a name="basics"></a><a href="Theweb-basics.htm">Basic Internet
Resources</a></h3>
How the web works, where it came from, how to find information on the
web,
and how to develop your own pages.
<h3><a name="thinking"></a><a href="Theweb-thinking.htm">Thinking About
the
Internet</a></h3>
Deep thoughts about the web and its implications for humanity and
knowledge.
<h3><a name="pedagogy"></a><a href="Theweb-pedagogy.htm">Internet
Pedagogy</a></h3>
Special resources for those who use the web in their teaching or wish
to
do so.
